content:
Start a Messaging Session with a Customer

Proactively start messaging sessions with customers in Service Cloud by sending them a message. Agent-initiated outbound messaging is available in all Messaging channels except Messaging for Web.

To initiate messaging sessions, you need:

* Available in: Lightning Experience
* This article applies to: Messaging for In-App, standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel
* User permissions needed:
	+ Agent Initiated Outbound Messaging AND Messaging Agent (for standard channels)
	+ Initiate Messaging Sessions AND Messaging Agent (for enhanced channels and Messaging for In-App)

To use the Send Message global action:

1. Use the Send Message global action to start a messaging session with a customer.
2. Agents can only initiate enhanced messaging sessions with a customer if the customer has a messaging user record that's linked to the desired messaging channel.

From any page in Salesforce, click the Send Message button and follow these steps:

1. Select a recipient (lookup an account, lead, contact, or messaging user).
2. Select a messaging channel.
3. Enter your message.
4. Click Send.

When initiating messaging sessions, keep these considerations in mind:

* In enhanced WhatsApp channels, if more than 24 hours have passed since the selected messaging user's last message, agents can't write freeform messages.
* In Messaging for In-App, if the customer responds, it's routed to your support team according to your channel routing logic.

In a Standard Messaging Channel from a Messaging User Record:

1. Use the Start Conversation record action on a messaging user record to start a messaging session with a customer.
2. Click Start Conversation and wait for the customer to respond.

If you don't see the Start Conversation button, possible reasons include:

* The user opted out of receiving messages.
* You're not assigned to the queue that's associated with the channel.
* Agent-initiated outbound messaging isn't supported in the channel.

To view the Start Conversation button on a person account or contact record, the person account or contact must be associated with the messaging user record.
title: Starting a Messaging Session with Customers
